reviews.review: I love Star Wars and found so much wasted potential here. The Rise of Skywalker is a hollow movie with bad writing and whole scenes and characters that seem to have come out of a board room, designed to please every shareholder and sell merchandise. It thinks we won't ask questions, since it blasts us with fast-paced scenes in the face like a hose. As a Star Wars movie, it is disrespectful to the achievements of the prior films. Anakin's bringing balance to the force didn't matter anymore. The Last Jedi apparently didn't happen. Characters that were introduced with promise end up doing nothing. I grew up with Star Wars, so this is personal. This movie was an embarrassment.
This movie is overrated. It did not really touched me. How could they failed to make it fresh since this is gigantic film.
It pains me to give it a pass. But the film has serious pacing issues
I was pretty excited and at although some was anticipated there was a few I expected turn of events, loved it
Loved all of it. I will miss Star Wars.
Thought the final saga provided a lot of closure. Great action and storyline. A must see
it was awesome!! can't wait to watch it again!!
Better than the last two installments.

The special effects were great, but it ends there. The script is horribleâ€” awful dialogue and plotting. The Voldermort (Palpatine) is back story doesn't work. And where's the humor?? The best parts of the early Star Wars episodes were the humor & character development along with the tension between Hans, Lea, Luke, R2D2, C3PO and Chewy. The new episodes are all serious and no fun. The Rise of Skywalker is possibly worse than any prior Star Wars "episode." It ends a legendary franchise with a thud.

It was good movie overall. Usual Star Wars storyline. Nothing new about this. It falls in between trying to please fans and appeal general audience and in the end does both underwhelmingly.
